2.2

In a test of the alternatives Ho: beta1 0 versus Ha: beta1 > 0, an analyst concluded Ho. Does this mean there is no linear association between X and Y?

I would say that it doesnt mean the association is not linear or that there is no linear association. It could be that the association is linear and negative (i.e.that X and Y are negatively correlated in a linear way).

2.17

The alpha level used was greater than .033. If the alpha had been .01, then the appropriate conclusion would have been Ho.
